<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-29-0022 </DOCNO><TEXT>Current procedures for estimating site-specific ground motions in thefree field during earthquakes are evaluated using acceleration data recordedat a number of sites in Mexico City during the September 19, 1985 Mexicanearthquake. A procedure for estimating seismic response when there issignificant soil-structure interaction is also evaluated using data fromsimulated earthquake shaking of centrifuged models. 19 references, 25figures, 1 table.</TEXT></DOC>